Our competition is tomorrow, and for some reason our elevator.setHeight pid command does not run when I mapped it to our controller.b button. Can someone see if I’m making a dumb mistake that I haven’t found yet? It seems like the run.until command isnt running at all even though I printed and confirmed the error between the current pos and the goal pos is greater than the error threshold. Thank you! here is our GitHub link: 3984-Reefscape-v1/Reefscape/src/main/java/frc/robot/subsystems/Elevator.java at main · Happyjog/3984-Reefscape-v1 · GitHub

Your button mapping creates a new InstantCommand that calls the setHeight method once, rather than mapping the button to the command returned by setHeight.

The mapping should look like:
driver.b().onTrue(s_Elevator.setHeight(Constants.Elevator.elevatorShaft.kLEVEL2));
